        <h2>The Healthcare Cost Problem Facing Employers</h2>

        <p>Healthcare costs continue to rise. The average employer-sponsored family health plan now exceeds $24,000 annually. Premiums increase 5-8% each year. And with the <a href="/aca-2026-guide/">ACA subsidy cliff in 2026</a>, employees who rely on marketplace coverage face premium hikes of 15-25%.</p>

        <p>Most employers feel stuck: raise premiums and risk losing talent, or absorb costs and strain budgets. But there is a third path -- <strong>supplemental Section 125 plans that reduce costs for both employer and employee</strong> while adding tangible benefits.</p>

