        <h2>How Section 125 Plans Reduce Healthcare Costs</h2>

        <p>A Section 125 plan (also called a cafeteria plan) allows employees to pay for certain benefits using pre-tax dollars. This creates savings at two levels:</p>

        <h3>For Employers: FICA Tax Reduction</h3>
        <p>When employees contribute to benefits pre-tax, their taxable wages decrease. Employers pay 7.65% FICA tax on wages, so every pre-tax dollar reduces the employer's FICA obligation. Across a workforce, this adds up significantly.</p>

        <div class="solution-highlight">
          <h3>The FICA Savings Mechanism</h3>
          <div class="solution-steps">
            <div class="step">
              <div class="step-number">1</div>
              <div class="step-content">
                <h4>Employee Enrolls in Supplemental Plan</h4>
                <p>Benefits are deducted pre-tax from each paycheck, reducing the employee's taxable wages.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="step">
              <div class="step-number">2</div>
              <div class="step-content">
                <h4>Taxable Wages Decrease</h4>
                <p>Lower taxable wages mean both employer and employee pay less in FICA taxes (7.65% each).</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="step">
              <div class="step-number">3</div>
              <div class="step-content">
                <h4>Savings Accumulate Per Employee</h4>
                <p>Optiv Health Benefits structures plans to maximize this reduction, generating $600-900 in employer savings per employee per year.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
