        <h3>For Employees: Free Benefits + Higher Take-Home Pay</h3>
        <p>Employees benefit in two ways. First, pre-tax contributions reduce their taxable income, increasing take-home pay. Second, supplemental plans from Optiv Health Benefits include tangible benefits at no additional out-of-pocket cost:</p>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>1,000+ free generic medications</strong> at $0 copay -- covering common prescriptions that employees would otherwise pay for out of pocket</li>
          <li><strong>24/7 telehealth access</strong> -- unlimited consultations with licensed physicians, anytime, from anywhere</li>
          <li><strong>Preventive care coverage</strong> -- routine health services that catch problems early and reduce long-term costs</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Why Not Just Cut Benefits to Save Money?</h2>

        <p>Cutting benefits backfires. Research consistently shows that reducing healthcare coverage leads to:</p>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>Higher turnover:</strong> Employees leave for companies with better packages. Replacement costs average $15,000 per employee.</li>
          <li><strong>Lower productivity:</strong> Employees without adequate coverage skip preventive care, leading to more sick days.</li>
          <li><strong>Harder recruiting:</strong> Benefits rank as a top-3 factor in job decisions for most employees.</li>
          <li><strong>Larger claims later:</strong> Deferred care results in costlier emergency treatment that hits group plan premiums.</li>
        </ul>

        <p>Section 125 supplemental plans solve this by <strong>adding</strong> value rather than removing it. Employers save money through the tax structure, not by making employees pay more.</p>

